"n.慷慨，大方 【英】 n. 慷慨，大方(willingn ess to share; unselfishness) 【考】 courage : rashness / generosity : prodigality(勇气过分是鲁莽/慷 慨过分是挥霍) 【记】 来自 generous(慷慨的) n. 慷慨大方 = unselfishness; (思想或行为的)崇高 = magnanimity 【类】courage: rashness = generosity: prodigality勇气过分是鲁莽 = 慷慨过分是挥霍 【记】来自generous 大方；general 有将军，长，头的意思→当老板，头的总是慷慨大方的 generosity (n.)  early 15c., ""nobility, goodness of race,"" from Latin generositatem (nominative generositas) ""nobility, excellence, magnanimity,"" from generosus (see generous). Meaning ""munificence"" is recorded from 1670s."
